<title>UK: Pearson off on profit-taking after rally.</title>
<headline>Pearson off on profit-taking after rally.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-08-14</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares in British media and leisure company Pearson Plc fell on Thursday on profit-taking, analysts said.</p>
<p>By 1459 GMT the stock was down 23p, or almost three percent, to 758-1/2p.</p>
<p>&quot;They have had a fantastic run, it is just profit- taking,&quot; said one analyst.</p>
<p>In the last two weeks, the stock has lept up nearly 20 percent, following higher-than-expected first-half profits, to challenge levels not seen mid-March.</p>
